- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing tasks such as part-of-speech tagging.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of multi-task learning and auxiliary losses to improve the performance of the model.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with developing new methods for improving the performance of a machine learning model.
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper discusses the use of neural networks for developing character-level word representations.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a less likely category as the paper does not deal with image or video data, but it is still possible as the paper discusses the use of neural networks for developing word representations.
